{{Infobox football biography | name = Marvin Zeegelaar | image = Marvin Zeegelaar.jpg | image_size = | caption = Zeegelaar in 2013 | fullname = Marvin Romeo Kwasie Zeegelaar<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/612828|title=Updated squads for 2017/18 Premier League confirmed|publisher=Premier League|date=2 February 2018|accessdate=17 February 2018}}</ref> | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1990|8|12|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Amsterdam]], Netherlands | height = 1.86 m | position = [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|Left back]] / [[Midfielder]] | currentclub = [[Udinese Calcio|Udinese]] (on loan from [[Watford F.C.|Watford]]) | clubnumber = 90 | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = [[FC Volendam|Volendam]] | youthyears2 = 2006–2009 | youthclubs2 = [[Jong Ajax|Ajax]] | years1 = 2009–2011 | clubs1 = [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]] | caps1 = 4 | goals1 = 0 | years2 = 2011 | clubs2 = → [[SBV Excelsior|Excelsior]] (loan) | caps2 = 12 | goals2 = 0 | years3 = 2011–2012 | clubs3 = [[RCD Espanyol B|Espanyol B]] | caps3 = 5 | goals3 = 0 | years4 = 2012–2014 | clubs4 = [[Elazığspor]] | caps4 = 34 | goals4 = 0 | years5 = 2013 | clubs5 = → [[Blackpool F.C.|Blackpool]] (loan) | caps5 = 2 | goals5 = 0 | years6 = 2014–2015 | clubs6 = [[Rio Ave F.C.|Rio Ave]] | caps6 = 37 | goals6 = 4 | years7 = 2016–2017 | clubs7 = [[Sporting CP]] | caps7 = 31 | goals7 = 0 | years8 = 2017– | clubs8 = [[Watford F.C.|Watford]] | caps8 = 12 | goals8 = 0 | years9= 2019– | clubs9 = → [[Udinese Calcio|Udinese]] (loan) | caps9 = 1 | goals9 = 0 | totalcaps = | totalgoals = | club-update = 26 January 2019 | nationalteam-update = }} '''Marvin Romeo Kwasie Zeegelaar''' (born 12 August 1990) is a Dutch professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for Italian club [[Udinese Calcio]] on loan from [[Watford F.C.|Watford]] as a [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|left back]] or a [[Midfielder#Wide midfielder|left midfielder]].
==Club career== Born in [[Amsterdam]] of [[Suriname]]se descent, Zeegelaar finished his formation with local [[AFC Ajax]]. He made his competitive debut on 12 November 2008, coming on as a [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] for [[Siem de Jong]] in [[2008–09 KNVB Cup|a match]] against [[FC Volendam]] for the [[KNVB Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ajaxmedia.nl/nieuws/spelers/zeegelaar-kan-contract-voorstel-verwachten|title=Zeegelaar kan contract-voorstel verwachten|trans-title=Zeegelaar expects contract offer|publisher=AFC Ajax|language=nl|date=12 November 2008|accessdate=26 December 2008}}</ref>
In the 2011 January [[transfer window]], Zeegelaar was loaned to fellow [[Eredivisie]] club [[SBV Excelsior]], appearing regularly and helping his team avoid relegation in [[2010–11 Eredivisie|the playoffs]]. In the summer, he signed a four-year contract with [[RCD Espanyol]] in Spain, being assigned to [[RCD Espanyol B|the B-team]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vi.nl/Nieuws-item/202082/Aanvaller-Zeegelaar-verruilt-Ajax-voor-Espanyol-B.htm|title=Aanvaller Zeegelaar verruilt Ajax voor Espanyol B|trans-title=Defender Zeegelaar swaps Ajax for Espanyol B|publisher=[[Voetbal International]]|language=nl|date=2011|accessdate=15 June 2011}}</ref>
In 2012, Zeegelaar joined [[Süper Lig]] side [[Elazığspor]]. In September of the following year, he moved to [[Blackpool F.C.|Blackpool]] in the [[EFL Championship|Championship]] on loan.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blackpoolfc.co.uk/news/article/zeegelaar-arrives-on-loan-1032672.aspx|title=Zeegelaar arrives on loan|publisher=Blackpool F.C|date=3 September 2013|accessdate=16 September 2013}}</ref>
In the summer of 2014, Zeegelaar signed a two-year contract with [[Rio Ave F.C.]] from the Portuguese [[Primeira Liga]]. He made his debut in the competition on 21 September, playing the second half of the 1–2 home loss to [[F.C. Arouca]];<ref>{{cite web|url=https://desporto.sapo.pt/futebol/jogo/rio-ave-vs-arouca-89780|title=Rio Ave 1–2 Arouca|publisher=[[SAPO (company)|SAPO]]|language=pt|date=21 September 2014|accessdate=6 September 2017}}</ref> he finished [[2014–15 Primeira Liga|his first season]] with 25 matches and one goal,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://desporto.sapo.ao/futebol/primeira-liga/artigos/rio-ave-e-nacional-empatam|title=Rio Ave e Nacional empatam|trans-title=Rio Ave and Nacional draw|publisher=SAPO|language=pt|date=9 March 2015|accessdate=6 September 2017}}</ref> helping to a final tenth position.
With only six months to go before he became a [[free agent]], Rio Ave accepted [[Sporting CP]]'s bid of [[Euro|€]]400.000 in November 2015, and Zeegelaar penned a three-and-a-half-year deal which became effective in the following [[transfer window]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.dn.pt/desporto/sporting/interior/zeegelaar-chega-a-alvalade-em-janeiro-por-400-mil-euros-4882817.html|title=Zeegelaar chega a Alvalade em janeiro por 400 mil euros|trans-title=Zeegelaar arrives at Alvalade in January for 400 thousand euros|newspaper=[[Diário de Notícias]]|first1=Bruno|last1=Pires|first2=Nuno|last2=Fernandes|language=pt|date=13 November 2015|accessdate=6 January 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://rr.sapo.pt/noticia/42011/sem_dizer_o_nome_jesus_confirma_zeegelaar|title=Sem dizer o nome, Jesus confirma Zeegelaar|trans-title=Without saying name, Jesus confirms Zeegelaar|publisher=[[Rádio Renascença]]|language=pt|date=15 December 2015|accessdate=6 January 2016}}</ref> In his only [[2016–17 Primeira Liga|full season]], he made 26 appearances across all competitions to help to a final third position, battling for position with Brazilian [[Jefferson Nascimento]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-nos/sporting/detalhe/jefferson-ou-zeegelaar-decide-jesus.html|title=Jefferson ou Zeegelaar? Decide Jesus|trans-title=Jefferson or Zeegelaar? Jesus decides|newspaper=[[Record (newspaper)|Record]]|first=António|last=Adão Farias|language=pt|date=8 February 2017|accessdate=6 January 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://desporto.sapo.pt/futebol/primeira-liga/artigos/sporting-perto-de-vender-marwin-zeegelaar-ao-sevilha-por-3-milhoes-de-euros|title=Sporting perto de vender Marvin Zeegelaar ao Sevilha por 3 milhões de euros|trans-title=Sporting close to selling Marvin Zeegelaar to Sevilla for 3 million euros|publisher=SAPO|language=pt|date=15 August 2017|accessdate=6 September 2017}}</ref>
On 31 August 2017, [[Watford F.C.|Watford]] signed Zeegelaar on a four-year contract.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.watfordfc.com/teams/first-team/official-hornets-sign-zeegelaar|title=Hornets sign Zeegelaar|publisher=Watford F.C|date=31 August 2017|accessdate=31 August 2017}}</ref> He made his [[Premier League]] debut on 19 November, playing the full 90 minutes in a 2–0 home win over [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/41958413|title=Watford 2–0 West Ham United|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|first=Greg|last=O'Keeffe|date=19 November 2017|accessdate=27 November 2017}}</ref>
On 10 January 2019, Zeegelaar joined Italian [[Serie A]] team [[Udinese Calcio]] on a five-month loan.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.tuttomercatoweb.com/serie-a/ufficiale-udinese-preso-zeegelaar-in-prestito-fino-a-giugno-1200345|title=UFFICIALE: Udinese, preso Zeegelaar in prestito fino a giugno|trans-title=OFFICIAL: Udinese, Zeegelaar acquired on loan until June|publisher=Tutto Mercato Web|first=Lorenzo|last=Di Benedetto|language=it|date=10 January 2019|accessdate=10 January 2019}}</ref>
==International career== In November 2016, 26-year-old Zeegelaar received his first call-up to the senior [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands squad]], for matches against [[Belgium national football team|Belgium]] and [[Luxembourg national football team|Luxembourg]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espnfc.com/world-cup-qualifying-uefa/story/2988772/arjen-robben-returns-to-netherlands-squad-for-belgium-and-luxembourg-games|title=Arjen Robben returns to Netherlands squad for Belgium, Luxembourg games|publisher=[[ESPN FC]]|date=4 November 2016|accessdate=7 November 2016}}</ref>
